commentary: Usman Shinwari to Tharanga, OUT Usman strikes with his second ball on ODI debut. He storms through the defences of Tharanga and pegs the middle stump back. Bowled through the gate. This is an excellent delivery: full and skids back into the left hander. The speedgun reads 137ks but it looked quicker than that, beating Tharanga, who dared to play across the line. He does not make contact. Usman hits

commentary: Imad Wasim to Chandimal, OUT An awful mix-up between the wickets! Short midwicket fumbles. Farcical cricket all around. Awful throw. Sarfraz runs in front of the stumps, gathers the throw, flings himself forward, and catches Chandimal short at the striker's end. This was slid through on middle, Chandimal skipped out and clipped it away to shortmidwicket's right, who misfields. Chandimal is more than halfway down the pitch. Thirimanne sells him down the river. Sarfraz made that throw from Shehzad look a lot better
